# Template URLs — not meant to resolve until the referenced infra is created.
# Each regex is matched against the full URL; one per line.
# Remove entries as the underlying targets are created.

# Phase 15 will create the `forge-reference-deployments` GitHub org. Until
# then, URLs like `https://github.com/forge-reference-deployments/<lib-name>`
# (lychee strips the `<lib-name>` placeholder and tries to resolve the org
# root, which 404s) are template placeholders in plan docs, not real links.
^https://github\.com/forge-reference-deployments/.*$

# opentelemetry.io hosts the authoritative OTel semantic-conventions spec.
# The site's CDN intermittently rate-limits or TLS-rejects requests from
# GitHub Actions runners, producing transient "Connection failed" /
# "TLS handshake failed" errors on PR CI runs while returning 200/301 for
# everyone else (verified via curl outside CI). The URLs below are
# referenced in docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-19-09-otel-genai-semconv-design.md
# as normative references; removing them would lose auditability, and the
# stable docs path is a strong guarantee they'll keep resolving. Ignoring
# them in lychee while keeping the reference is the pragmatic trade-off.
# Revisit: if OTel moves their specs site, drop these and re-verify.
^https://opentelemetry\.io/docs/specs/semconv/.*$
